This place is hardly ever busy, and for good reason. When I place my order online, they either haven't started it until I arrive, or it's wrong, or both.  But the food is terrible. I ordered a "Fireball." What an awful thing. Italian meatballs, chili with BEANS in it and pickled jalapenos. Who the hell would invent such a thing? Who would want kidney beans and pickled jalapenos with their Italian meatballs? (And shame on me for assuming the chili wouldn't have beans and the peppers would be the more-appropriate banana peppers.)  And their "Biggs" are about 2/3rds the size of a Subway footlong. I'll stick with more boring Subway or the more expensive Atrium Cafe.

There are enough great local sandwich shops (Sundevich in nearby Blagden Alley, G by Mike Isabella, to name a few) that you'd think chains like Potbellys won't do well. However, they do own a space in downtown DC because they 1) cater for large groups, 2) create tasty breakfast and lunch sandwiches quickly, and 3) the chocolate chip cookies. Even if you don't love sandwiches, those cookies. Baked with oatmeal, the chocolate chips really pop. They have large cookies, mini cookies, and cookies for everyone in a bag. Stop by during your next chocolate craving.
